1.What is a Subnet?
  A subnet, or subnetwork ,is a logical subdivision of an IP network,dividing a large network into smaller,managable,and more efficient parts.
2. What is a Subnet Mask?
 A subnet mask is a 32-bit number used in IPv4 networking that defines which part of an IP address refers to the network(network ID) and which part refers to the individual device(host ID).
3.what is a CIDR notation?(e.g.,192.168.1.0/24)
  CIDR is a compact way to represent an IP address and its associated network mask,writtenn as a.b.c.d/n. The suffix /n indicated the number of bits (1s) in the subnet mask.
4.Why do we need Subnetting?
  Subnetting is required to break large,inefficient networks into smaller,managable ,and secure subnetworks(subnets).it improves network performance by reducing broadcast traffic congestion,
enhances security through isolation,and conserves limited IPv4 address spaces by allocating resources more efficiently.

